South Africa has recorded 215,855 COVID-19 cases with 3,502 and 102,299 recoveries. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Health Minister Zweli Mkhize says South Africa is now approaching the COVID-19 peak. Mkhize is urging people to continue following precautionary measures. The country has recorded 224,665 COVID-19 cases with 3,600 deaths and 106,842 recoveries. READ: COVID-19: Mass gravesites prepared in Gauteng Mkhize further stated that Gauteng is expected to be the next COVID-19 epicentre in South Africa. As of Tuesday, the total number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in Gauteng is 75,015, with 19,799 recoveries and 478 deaths. Mkhize paid tribute to health workers who are on the frontline of fighting the coronavirus. READ: COVID-19: Frontline workers risking their lives to save ours The minister says their contribution is appreciated and that interventions have been put in place to address infections among health care workers. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.